                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>@Check[type:will|dc:30] saving throw. On a failure, the creature who killed the cursed king becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1}. On a critical failure, it becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2}. As long as that creature remains cursed, it can't remove or decrease the value of the stupefied condition in any way. Afflicted creatures must attempt the saving throw again every 24 hours, increasing the stupefied condition by 1 on a failure or 2 on a critical failure. If the condition ever increases past @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 4}, they transform, body and mind, into the same animal as the cursed king's head, similar to the critical failure effect of <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Baleful Polymorph]</em>.</p>"
